text: IFK Jönköping was a sports club in the town of Jönköping in Sweden. Its women's soccer team played in the Swedish second division during the 1990's. The club was established in 1989 out of IK Tord's women's soccer section. The club won the women's Småland district championship in the years of 1994, 1995 and 1997. The women's soccer team was dissolved before the 1997. The activity was then transferred over to IFK Öxnehaga. ==References== Category:Sport in Jönköping Category:1989 establishments in Sweden Category:1998 establishments in Europe Category:Swedish football clubs
